TY  - JOUR
T1  - Ambiguity Aversion, Robustness, and the Variational Representation of Preferences
AU  - Maccheroni, Fabio
AU  - Marinacci, Massimo
AU  - Rustichini, Aldo
Y1  - 2006/11/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/11/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00716.x
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1447
EP  - 1498
VL  - 74
IS  - 6
KW  - Ambiguity aversion
KW  - model uncertainty
KW  - robustness
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00716.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We characterize, in the Anscombe?Aumann framework, the preferences for which there are a utility functionu on outcomes and an ambiguity indexc on the set of probabilities on the states of the world such that, for all acts f and g, . The function u represents the decision maker's risk attitudes, while the index c captures his ambiguity attitudes. These preferences include the multiple priors preferences of Gilboa and Schmeidler and the multiplier preferences of Hansen and Sargent. This provides a rigorous decision-theoretic foundation for the latter model, which has been widely used in macroeconomics and finance.
ER  - 

