TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Folk Theorem for Games with Private Almost-Perfect Monitoring
AU  - Hörner, Johannes
AU  - Olszewski, Wojciech
Y1  - 2006/11/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/11/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00717.x
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1499
EP  - 1544
VL  - 74
IS  - 6
KW  - Repeated games
KW  - private monitoring
KW  - folk theorem
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00717.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We prove the folk theorem for discounted repeated games under private, almost-perfect monitoring. Our result covers all finite, n-player games that satisfy the usual full-dimensionality condition. Mixed strategies are allowed in determining the individually rational payoffs. We assume no cheap-talk communication between players and no public randomization device.
ER  - 

